tent\":\"<p>Diagnostic test evaluating specific tracts of the central and peripheral nervous system. May include visual, auditory, or somatosensory evoked potentials. These record the electrical responses of the brain and spinal cord to the stimulation of the senses.<\\/p>\",\"_id\":\"e441933\"},{\"tab_title\":\"Polysomnography\",\"tab_content\":\"<p>A type of sleep study employed to diagnose disorders associated with abnormal sleep behavior<\\/p><p>Intraoperative monitoring, Intraoperative neurophysiologic monitoring<\\/p>\",\"_id\":\"72e64d0\"}]},\"elements\":[],\"widgetType\":\"accordion\"}],\"isInner\":false}],\"isInner\":false},{\"id\":\"cce794d\",\"elType\":\"section\",\"settings\":[],\"elements\":[{\"id\":\"5ba7b81\",\"elType\":\"column\",\"settings\":{\"_column_size\":100},\"elements\":[{\"id\":\"a5b2ac6\",\"elType\":\"widget\",\"settings\":{\"style\":\"double\",\"weight\":{\"unit\":\"px\",\"size\":3},\"color\":\"#36afe2\"},\"elements\":[],\"widgetType\":\"divider\"}],\"isInner\":false}],\"isInner\":false},{\"id\":\"b1a249d\",\"elType\":\"section\",\"settings\":{\"structure\":\"33\"},\"elements\":[{\"id\":\"69e895d\",\"elType\":\"column\",\"settings\":{\"_column_size\":25,\"_inline_size\":null},\"elements\":[],\"isInner\":false},{\"id\":\"1507318\",\"elType\":\"column\",\"settings\":{\"_column_size\":50,\"_inline_size\":null},\"elements\":[{\"id\":\"fe96ca6\",\"elType\":\"widget\",\"settings\":{\"title\":\"Electrodiagnostic Medicine\"},\"elements\":[],\"widgetType\":\"heading\"}],\"isInner\":false},{\"id\":\"7f4bbac\",\"elType\":\"column\",\"settings\":{\"_column_size\":25,\"_inline_size\":null},\"elements\":[],\"isInner\":false}],\"isInner\":false},{\"id\":\"858fa04\",\"elType\":\"section\",\"settings\":{\"structure\":\"20\"},\"elements\":[{\"id\":\"2d96033\",\"elType\":\"column\",\"settings\":{\"_column_size\":50,\"_inline_size\":null},\"elements\":[{\"id\":\"28e33c4\",\"elType\":\"widget\",\"settings\":{\"editor\":\"<p>Electrodiagnostic medicine is a subset of clinical neurophysiology. Electrodiagnostic medicine focuses only on the peripheral nervous system and not the central nervous system. Whereas a clinical neurophysiologist is trained to perform all the following studies EEG, intraoperative monitoring, nerve conduction studies, EMG and evoked potentials, and electrodiagnostic physician focuses mainly on nerve conduction studies, needle EMG, and evoked potentials.<\\/p>\"},\"elements\":[],\"widgetType\":\"text-editor\"}],\"isInner\":false},{\"id\":\"8ae643c\",\"elType\":\"column\",\"settings\":{\"_column_size\":50,\"_inline_size\":null},\"elements\":[{\"id\":\"5c8a2be\",\"elType\":\"widget\",\"settings\":{\"editor\":\"<p>The American Board of Psychiatry and Neurology provides certification examination in clinical neurophysiology. The American Board of Electrodiagnostic Medicine provides certification in EDX medicines.The American Board of Clinical Neurophysiology certifies in electroencephalography (EEG), Evoked Potentials (EP), Polysomnography (PSG), Epilepsy Monitoring, and Neurologic Intraoperative Monitoring (NIOM). In the US physicians typically specialize in EEG or EDX medicine but not both.<\\/p>\"},\"elements\":[],\"widgetType\":\"text-editor\"}],\"isInner\":false}],\"isInner\":false},{\"id\":\"8d1cf1f\",\"elType\":\"section\",\"settings\":[],\"elements\":[{\"id\":\"17443ed\",\"elType\":\"column\",\"settings\":{\"_column_size\":100},\"elements\":[{\"id\":\"1d007f5\",\"elType\":\"widget\",\"settings\":[],\"elements\":[],\"widgetType\":\"icon\"}],\"isInner\":false}],\"isInner\":false}]'),
