",\"elType\":\"widget\",\"settings\":{\"editor\":\"<p>The VEP measures the time that it takes for a visual stimulus to travel from the eye to the occipital cortex. It can give the doctor an idea of whether the nerve pathways are abnormal in any way. For example, in multiple sclerosis, the insulating layer around nerve cells in the brain and spinal cord (known as the myelin sheath) can be affected. This means that it takes a longer time for electrical signals to be conducted from the eyes, resulting in an abnormal VEP. A normal VEP can be fairly sensitive in excluding a lesion of the optic nerve, along its pathways in the anterior part of the brain.<\\/p>\"},\"elements\":[],\"widgetType\":\"text-editor\"}],\"isInner\":false},{\"id\":\"c6c5eee\",\"elType\":\"column\",\"settings\":{\"_column_size\":50,\"_inline_size\":null},\"elements\":[{\"id\":\"044011b\",\"elType\":\"widget\",\"settings\":{\"carousel\":[{\"id\":108,\"url\":\"http:\\/\\/localhost:81\\/clevelandneurocare\\/wp-content\\/uploads\\/2019\\/02\\/neurophysiology1.jpg\"},{\"id\":76,\"url\":\"http:\\/\\/localhost:81\\/clevelandneurocare\\/wp-content\\/uploads\\/2019\\/02\\/Longterm-EEG.jpg\"},{\"id\":72,\"url\":\"http:\\/\\/localhost:81\\/clevelandneurocare\\/wp-content\\/uploads\\/2019\\/02\\/Clinical-Neurophysiology.jpg\"}],\"thumbnail_size\":\"medium\",\"slides_to_show\":\"1\",\"navigation\":\"none\",\"autoplay_speed\":500,\"effect\":\"fade\"},\"elements\":[],\"widgetType\":\"image-carousel\"}],\"isInner\":false}],\"isInner\":false},{\"id\":\"1fb190b\",\"elType\":\"section\",\"settings\":[],\"elements\":[{\"id\":\"c427a68\",\"elType\":\"column\",\"settings\":{\"_column_size\":100},\"elements\":[{\"id\":\"317dc3d\",\"elType\":\"widget\",\"settings\":{\"weight\":{\"unit\":\"px\",\"size\":2},\"color\":\"#6ec1e4\"},\"elements\":[],\"widgetType\":\"divider\"}],\"isInner\":false}],\"isInner\":false}]'),
