(20, 1, '2019-02-17 06:56:03', '2019-02-17 06:56:03', '<figure><img src=\"http://www.clevelandneurocare.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/02/ECG-768x583.png\" alt=\"ECG\" /></figure><figure><img src=\"http://www.clevelandneurocare.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/02/ECG1.jpg\" alt=\"ECG1\" /></figure><figure><img src=\"http://www.clevelandneurocare.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/02/ECG3.jpg\" alt=\"ECG3\" /></figure><figure><img src=\"http://www.clevelandneurocare.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/02/Electical-Systems.jpg\" alt=\"Anterior cut of heart showing normal, healthy heart and conduction system with arrows; ACardio_20140401_v1_001.ai\nSOURCE: cardiacsurg_maze_proc_1a_layers.psd; cardiacsurg_maze_proc_1b_layers.psd; cardiasurg_maze_anat.ai\" /></figure>			\n			<h5>Whats is an ECG (electrocardiogram)? </h5>		\n		<p>An electrocardiogram (ECG) is a test which measures the electrical activity of your heart to show whether or not it is working normally.</p><p>An ECG records the hearts rhythm and activity on a moving strip of paper or a line on a screen. Your doctor can read and interpret the peaks and dips on paper or screen to see if there is any abnormal or unusual activity.</p>		\n			<h5>What can an ECG show?</h5>		\n		<p>An electrocardiogram can be a useful way to find out whether your high blood pressure has caused any damage to your heart or blood vessels. Because of this, you may be asked to have an ECG when you are first diagnosed with high blood pressure.</p>		\n					<ul>\n							<li >\n										Cholesterol clogging up your hearts blood supply\n									</li>\n								<li >\n										A heart attack in the past\n									</li>\n								<li >\n										Enlargement of one side of the heart\n									</li>\n								<li >\n										Abnormal heart rhythms\n									</li>\n						</ul>\n										<img width=\"950\" height=\"567\" src=\"http://www.clevelandneurocare.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/02/ECG2.jpg\" alt=\"\" srcset=\"http://www.clevelandneurocare.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/02/ECG2.jpg 950w, http://www.clevelandneurocare.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/02/ECG2-300x179.jpg 300w, http://www.clevelandneurocare.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/02/ECG2-768x458.jpg 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 950px) 100vw, 950px\" />											\n										<img width=\"850\" height=\"639\" src=\"http://www.clevelandneurocare.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/02/ECG4.png\" alt=\"\" srcset=\"http://www.clevelandneurocare.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/02/ECG4.png 850w, http://www.clevelandneurocare.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/02/ECG4-300x226.png 300w, http://www.clevelandneurocare.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/02/ECG4-768x577.png 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 850px) 100vw, 850px\" />											\n										<img width=\"1024\" height=\"686\" src=\"http://www.clevelandneurocare.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/02/heart_inner_section-1024x686.jpg\" alt=\"\" srcset=\"http://www.clevelandneurocare.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/02/heart_inner_section-1024x686.jpg 1024w, http://www.clevelandneurocare.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/02/heart_inner_section-300x201.jpg 300w, http://www.clevelandneurocare.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/02/heart_inner_section-768x515.jpg 768w, http://www.clevelandneurocare.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/02/heart_inner_section.jpg 1500w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px\" />											\n										<img width=\"450\" height=\"332\" src=\"http://www.clevelandneurocare.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/02/pulmonary_circuit.gif\" alt=\"\" />', 'ECG', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'ecg', '', '', '2019-02-17 16:52:58', '2019-02-17 16:52:58', '', 0, 'http://www.clevelandneurocare.com/?page_id=20', 0, 'page', '', 0),
